    • Constructor Detail

      • CustomLeatherArmor

        public CustomLeatherArmor(ArmorType armorType,
                          int amount,
                          short durability,
                          String idName,
                          org.bukkit.Color color)
        Creates a Custom Leather Armor piece.
        Parameters:
        armorType - The type of the Leather Armor. This will automatically set the Material using ArmorType.getLeatherMaterial().
        amount - The amount of the Leather Armor. Recommended value is one, as Armor Pieces do not have a stackable size higher than 1 by default.
        durability - The durability of the Leather Armor.
        idName - the Custom Armor's ID Name. This MUST BE SIMILAR to "vanilla_additions:emerald_sword" and is saved in the ItemStack so you can easily detect which Custom Armor it is.
        color - The color that the leather armor will have.
